{"slideshow_credits": null, "snippet": "New research suggests that the leprosy parasite is a paradox encapsulated \u2014 at once rugged and feeble, exacting and inept.", "abstract": "Hansen's disease, or leprosy, continues to confound and surprise researchers, who describe the parasite that causes the disease as being at once feeble and hardy; leprosy, which is thought of by many as antiquated disease and may be oldest infectious disease to specifically attack humans, still strikes some 200,000 people a year, mainly in developing nations.", "section_name": "Science", "print_page": "1", "document_type": "article", "byline": {"person": [{"firstname": "Natalie", "role": "reported", "lastname": "ANGIER", "rank": 1, "organization": ""}], "original": "By NATALIE ANGIER", "contributor": ""}, "web_url": "http://www.nytimes.com/2014/07/01/science/leprosy-still-claiming-victims.html", "lead_paragraph": "New research suggests that the leprosy parasite is a paradox encapsulated \u2014 at once rugged and feeble, exacting and inept.", "headline": {"main": "Leprosy, Still Claiming Victims", "print_headline": "Leprosy, Still Claiming Victims"}, "_id": "53b1b06438f0d835aaa9b5d2", "word_count": "1637", "multimedia": [{"height": 126, "url": "images/2014/07/01/science/01leprosy/01leprosy-thumbWide.jpg", "legacy": {"wideheight": "126", "wide": "images/2014/07/01/science/01leprosy/01leprosy-thumbWide.jpg", "widewidth": "190"}, "subtype": "wide", "width": 190, "type": "image"}, {"height": 400, "url": "images/2014/07/01/science/01LEPR/01LEPR-articleLarge.jpg", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2014/07/01/science/01LEPR/01LEPR-articleLarge.jpg", "xlargewidth": "600", "xlargeheight": "400"}, "subtype": "xlarge", "width": 600, "type": "image"}, {"height": 75, "url": "images/2014/07/01/science/01LEPR/01LEPR-thumbStandard.jpg", "legacy": {"thumbnail": "images/2014/07/01/science/01LEPR/01LEPR-thumbStandard.jpg", "thumbnailwidth": "75", "thumbnailheight": "75"}, "subtype": "thumbnail", "width": 75, "t